brewery.brewery_description: Kindred Spirit Brewing is a craft brewery in Goochland, Virginia.  Independently owned and operated.  Beers for every palate. Stop by the taproom to see what new beers we have on tap.  Cheers!

beer.beer_description: Brewed with lactose sugar, coffe and vanilla beans and cacao nibs.  A coffee shake in a beer!
IPA with Thai chilis,ginger, lime, basil, orange peel and lemongrass.
Hazy IPA with Mosaic, Vic Secret and El Dorado Hops

This IPA uses all the same malts and hops as our flagship Headspace.  We switched the hops to mostly Citra and just a little Mosaic.  This beer boasts a ton of orange and tangerine on the nose with even more orange on the palate with a hint of rind bitterness.

Brewed in Collaboration with Fans of VA Craft Breweries founder David Hunter, this Baltic Porter is loaded with 75 pounds of toasted almonds.  Milk chocolate and almonds on the nose with flavors of chocolate, caramel and toffee leading to a smooth finish!
Easy drinking lager dry hopped with Citra
Barfly Bitter is our take on an English Mild. Light bodied and very sessionable, with a subtle sweet roastiness.
Mexican chocolate stout with pasilla and guadillo chili, cacao, vanilla, cinnamon and black beans.

Dark golden in color, this beer boasts strong herbal aromas with hints of pear. Peppery with some floral and dark fruit notes lead to a spicy dry finish. This beer was fermented using native yeast gathered from Swift Creek Berry Farm by RVA Yeast Labs!
